### JSON Response Parsing

All prompts that request JSON output use the following parsing logic:

```javascript
function parseJSONResponse(text) {
  try {
    // Try to extract JSON from markdown code blocks
    const jsonMatch = text.match(/```json\n([\s\S]*?)\n```/) || 
                     text.match(/```\n([\s\S]*?)\n```/) ||
                     text.match(/\[[\s\S]*\]/) ||
                     text.match(/\{[\s\S]*\}/);
    
    if (jsonMatch) {
      const jsonText = jsonMatch[1] || jsonMatch[0];
      return JSON.parse(jsonText);
    }
    
    // Try parsing entire text
    return JSON.parse(text);
  } catch (e) {
    console.error('Failed to parse JSON from response:', e);
    return null;
  }
}
```

---

### Prompt Refinement Patterns

#### Pattern 1: Iterative Refinement
```
User: "Make it more engaging"
System: Regenerate with focus on engagement hooks, questions, and CTAs
```

#### Pattern 2: Style Transfer
```
User: "Use the Educational Hook Style"
System: Regenerate description using that specific style template
```

#### Pattern 3: Context Addition
```
User: "Add more hashtags"
System: Generate additional hashtags maintaining relevance
```

#### Pattern 4: Tone Adjustment
```
User: "Make it more casual"
System: Regenerate with casual language, contractions, emojis
```

---

### Quality Assurance Checklist

For each prompt:
- ✅ Includes user context (niche, goal)
- ✅ Requests structured output (JSON when applicable)
- ✅ Specifies length/format constraints
- ✅ Includes examples or templates
- ✅ Has clear success criteria
- ✅ Handles edge cases
- ✅ Provides fallback options

---

### Performance Optimization

#### Token Management
- Keep prompts concise but complete
- Remove unnecessary context when possible
- Use variables efficiently

#### Response Formatting
- Always request JSON for structured data
- Provide clear examples in prompts
- Specify field types and constraints

#### Caching Strategy
- Cache common queries (description styles, niche info)
- Store user preferences
- Reuse context across requests

---

### Content Guidelines

All prompts enforce:
- ✅ Compliance with YouTube Community Guidelines
- ✅ Original and authentic content
- ✅ No copyrighted material
- ✅ Truthful and accurate information
- ✅ Respect for viewer privacy

